values.description: Target element to attach the paginator dropdown overlay, valid values are "body" or a local ng-template variable of another element (note: use binding with brackets for template variables, e.g. [appendTo]="mydiv" for a div element having #mydiv as variable name).

values.description: Template of the current page report element. Available placeholders are {currentPage},{totalPages},{rows},{first},{last} and {totalRecords}

values.description: Whether to display current page report.

values.name: showJumpToPageDropdown
values.description: Whether to display a dropdown to navigate to any page.

values.description: When enabled, icons are displayed on paginator to go first and last page.

values.name: showPageLinks
values.description: Whether to show page links.

values.name: defaultSortOrder
values.description: Sort order to use when an unsorted column gets sorted by user interaction.

values.name: sortMode
values.description: Defines whether sorting works on single column or on multiple columns.

values.name: resetPageOnSort
values.description: When true, resets paginator to first page after sorting.

values.name: customSort
values.description: Whether to use the default sorting or a custom one using sortFunction.

values.name: selectionMode
values.description: Specifies the selection mode, valid values are "single" and "multiple".

values.name: contextMenuSelection
values.description: Selected row with a context menu.

values.name: contextMenuSelectionMode
values.description: Mode of the contet menu selection.

values.name: dataKey
values.description: A property to uniquely identify a record in data.

values.name: metaKeySelection
values.description: Defines whether metaKey is should be considered for the selection. On touch enabled devices, metaKeySelection is turned off automatically.

values.name: compareSelectionBy
values.description: Algorithm to define if a row is selected, valid values are "equals" that compares by reference and "deepEquals" that compares all fields.

values.name: rowHover
values.description: Adds hover effect to rows without the need for selectionMode.

values.name: loading
values.description: Displays a loader to indicate data load is in progress.

values.name: loadingIcon
values.description: The icon to show while indicating data load is in progress.

values.name: showLoader
values.description: Whether to show the loading mask when loading property is true.

values.name: scrollable
values.description: When specifies, enables horizontal and/or vertical scrolling.

values.name: scrollHeight
values.description: Height of the scroll viewport in fixed pixels or the "flex" keyword for a dynamic size.

values.name: virtualScroll
values.description: Whether the data should be loaded on demand during scroll.

values.description: Height of a row to use in calculations of virtual scrolling.

values.name: virtualScrollOptions
values.description: Whether to use the scroller feature. The properties of scroller component can be used like an object in it.

values.name: virtualScrollDelay
values.description: The delay (in milliseconds) before triggering the virtual scroll. This determines the time gap between the user's scroll action and the actual rendering of the next set of items in the virtual scroll.

values.name: frozenWidth
values.description: Width of the frozen columns container.

values.name: frozenColumns
values.description: An array of objects to represent dynamic columns that are frozen.

values.name: resizableColumns
values.description: When enabled, columns can be resized using drag and drop.

values.name: columnResizeMode
values.description: Defines whether the overall table width should change on column resize, valid values are "fit" and "expand".

values.name: reorderableColumns
values.description: When enabled, columns can be reordered using drag and drop.

values.name: contextMenu
values.description: Local ng-template varilable of a ContextMenu.
